CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 17, 1965, pg. 24 reads: "Power Play - Two of the most feared hitters in baseball, Willie Mays (left) and Roberto Clemente, were in happy moods at Forbes Field, on Monday afternoon, as the Pirates and Giants opened the baseball season.  Both players are expected to play key roles in the pennant destinies of their respective teams. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: San Francisco Giants baseball player Willie Mays and Pittsburgh Pirates Roberto Clemente, posed on Forbes Field for 1965 season opener
